Nevertheless, CSL is expected to experience a 20% profit hike in FY24, with analysts predicting a potential year-end share price target. However, concerns persist regarding the company's health outlook, highlighting the mixed reactions to its latest financial results.

name: Tom Daley
summary: British diver Tom Daley, one of the country's most decorated athletes, has announced his retirement from the sport. Daley will continue to compete until the 2024 Paris Olympics, after which he plans to focus on his family and mental well-being. The decision comes after a career spanning nearly two decades, during which Daley became Britain's most decorated diver, winning multiple Olympic and world championship medals. He cited the toll that training and competition had taken on his physical and mental health as reasons for his retirement. Daley expressed gratitude for the support he had received throughout his career and emphasized the importance of prioritizing his well-being.

summary: Various seismic activity has been reported worldwide. In Canada, an unconfirmed earthquake was felt near Sudbury, Ontario. The largest seismic event was a powerful earthquake off Japan's coast, triggering a tsunami warning. Despite the magnitude, there is no tsunami threat to British Columbia. Meanwhile, Japan remains on edge as experts warn of a possible "megaquake." An earthquake in Syria rattled neighboring Israel and Lebanon, triggering memories of a deadly temblor last year. In Southern California, a magnitude 4.4 earthquake shook Los Angeles and San Diego, causing minor damage. Another 4.4 earthquake occurred in Los Angeles, centered on a known fault system.
